I could finally work out again last night. 30 minutes on the treadmill, alternating walk/jog (5/3.5 min respectively). Then I did some light weight work, and some ab/leg work (to help ease the back pain from the treadmill)Dammit, it seems like I not making any progress, weight-wise...but I am certainly getting more fit, cardio-wise. Before I couldn't jog more than 1/8 mile at a time. Now I can do a quarter mile pretty easily...and I'm not gasping like I'm going to die when I slow back down. I hate that I've had setbacks twice in the past year, both due to my back. I've got to figure out how to avoid hurting it. I feel like I should be much further along than this.
