So I was reading an NYT article about Obama's first full day, and I came across this photo. Several thoughts came to mind.I wonder if the more grizzled/experienced photographers trick the newbie photographers into taking really silly shots, by pretending that they'll be really compelling. I like to think so.Do all of these guys think that the guy taking a picture of them is a pretentious dick? At least a little bit?On the flip side, I hope that somewhere out there, you can find something like The Journal of Post-Modern Photojournalism and it'll have a photo of some guy taking a photo of four other guys taking photos of a pen.I had those thoughts last night, but I was already in bed so I didn't get up to post them. Today I was searching for the photo again and I found this photo (by the same photographer), which seems to lend credence to all of these ideas--Doug Mills is tricking the other photojournalists into creating self-referential photojournalism scenes for him to take pretentious pictures of. RabidGnome
